"Ghini R., Hamada E., Pedro Jr. M.J., Marengo J.A., Gonçalves R.R.D.V.","Risk analysis of climate change on coffee nematodes and leaf miner in Brazil",2008,"Pesquisa Agropecuaria Brasileira","43","2",,"187","194",,,10.1590/S0100-204X2008000200005,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-42449120631&partnerID=40&md5=89cec5d905b06cf376194c347d9d810f","Embrapa Meio Ambiente, Caixa Postal 69, CEP 13820-000 Jaguariúna, SP, Brazil; Instituto Agronômico, Caixa Postal 28, CEP 13001-970 Campinas, SP, Brazil; Centro de Previsão de Tempo e Estudos Climáticos, Rodovia Presidente Dutra, Km 40, CEP 12630-000 Cachoeira Paulista, SP, Brazil; Universidade Estadual de Campinas, Faculdade de Engenharia Agrícola, Caixa Postal 6011, CEP 13083-875 Campinas, SP, Brazil","Ghini, R., Embrapa Meio Ambiente, Caixa Postal 69, CEP 13820-000 Jaguariúna, SP, Brazil; Hamada, E., Embrapa Meio Ambiente, Caixa Postal 69, CEP 13820-000 Jaguariúna, SP, Brazil; Pedro Jr., M.J., Instituto Agronômico, Caixa Postal 28, CEP 13001-970 Campinas, SP, Brazil; Marengo, J.A., Centro de Previsão de Tempo e Estudos Climáticos, Rodovia Presidente Dutra, Km 40, CEP 12630-000 Cachoeira Paulista, SP, Brazil; Gonçalves, R.R.D.V., Universidade Estadual de Campinas, Faculdade de Engenharia Agrícola, Caixa Postal 6011, CEP 13083-875 Campinas, SP, Brazil","The objective of this work was to assess the potential impact of climate change on the spatial distribution of coffee nematodes (races of Meloidogyne incognita) and leaf miner (Leucoptera coffeella), using a Geographic Information System. Assessment of the impacts of climate change on pest infestations and disease epidemics in crops is needed as a basis for revising management practices to minimize crop losses as climatic conditions shift. Future scenarios focused on the decades of the 2020's, 2050's, and 2080's (scenarios A2 and B2) were obtained from five General Circulation Models available on Data Distribution Centre from Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change. Geographic distribution maps were prepared using models to predict the number of generations of the nematodes and leaf miner. Maps obtained in scenario A2 allowed prediction of an increased infestation of the nematode and of the pest, due to greater number of generations per month, than occurred under the climatological normal from 1961-1990. The number of generations also increased in the B2 scenario, but was lower than in the A2 scenario for both organisms.","Coffea arabica; Global warming; Leucoptera coffeella; Meloidogyne incognita; Pest zoning","Agromyzidae; Coffea arabica; Leucoptera coffeella; Meloidogyne incognita; Nematoda",,,,,,"ALFONSI, R.R., SENTELHAS, P.C., Estimativa da temperatura do solo através da temperatura do ar em abrigo meteorológico. (1996) Revista Brasileira de Agrometeorologia, 4, pp. 57-61; ASSAD, E.D., PINTO, H.S., ZULLO JÚNIOR, J., ÁVILA, A.M.H., Impacto das mudanças climáticas no zoneamento agroclimático do café no Brasil. (2004) Pesquisa Agropecuária Brasileira, 39, pp. 1057-1064; BERGOT, M., CLOPPET, E., PÉRARNAUD, V., DÉQUÉ, M., MARÇAIS, B., DESPREZ-LOUSTAU, M.L., Simulation of potential range expansion of oak disease caused by Phytophthora cinnamomi under climate change (2004) Global Change Biology, 10, pp. 1539-1552; CHAKRABORTY, S., Potential impact of climate change on plant-pathogen interactions (2005) Australasian Plant Pathology, 34, pp. 443-448; GALLO, D., NAKANO, O., SILVEIRA NETO, S., CARVALHO, R.P.L., BAPTISTA, G.C., BERTI FILHO, E., PARRA, J.R.P., OMOTO, C., (2002) Entomologia agrícola, , Piracicaba: Fealq, 920p; GARRETT, K.A., DENDY, S.P., FRANK, E.E., ROUSE, M.N., TRAVERS, S.E., Climate change effects on plant disease: Genomes to ecosystems (2006) Annual Review of Phytopathology, 44, pp. 489-509; GHINI, R., (2005) Mudanças climáticas globais e doenças de plantas, , Jaguariúna: Embrapa Meio Ambiente, 104p; GHINI, R., HAMADA, E., GONÇALVES, R.R.V., GASPAROTTO, L., PEREIRA, J.C.R., Análise de risco das mudanças climáticas globais sobre a sigatoka-negra da bananeira no Brasil. (2007) Fitopatologia Brasileira, 32, pp. 197-204; Climate, I.P.C.C., (2001) Change 2001: Synthesis report, , Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 398p; IPCC. Climate Change 2007: the physical science basis. Available at: http://ipcc-wg1.ucar.edu/wg1/wg1-report.html. Accessed on: 15 Aug. 2007SRES climate scenarios: The IPCC data distribution centre, , http://www.ipcc-data.org/sres/gcm_data.html, Available at:, Accessed on: 26 Apr. 2006; JAEHN, A., Determinação da constante térmica das raças 1, 2 e 4 de Meloidogyne incognita em cafeeiro. (1991) Nematologia Brasileira, 15, pp. 135-142; PARRA, J.R.P., Biologia comparada de Perileucoptera coffeella (Guérin-Mèneville, 1842) (Lepidoptera, Lyonetiidae) visando ao seu zoneamento ecológico no Estado de São Paulo. (1985) Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 29, pp. 45-76; RANDIG, O., CARNEIRO, R.M.D.G., CASTAGNONE-SERENO, P., Identificação das principais espécies de Meloidogyne parasitas do cafeeiro no Brasil com marcadores SCAR-café em Multiplex-PCR. (2004) Nematologia Brasileira, 28, pp. 1-10; REIS, P.R., SOUZA, J.C., Manejo integrado das pragas do cafeeiro em Minas Gerais. (1998) Informe Agropecuário, 19, pp. 17-25; SALAMA, H.S., HAMDY, M.K., EL-DIN, M.M., The thermal constant for timing the emergence of the red palm weevil, Rhynchophorus ferrugineus (Oliv.) (Coleoptera, Curculionidae) (2002) Journal of Pest Science, 75, pp. 26-29; SALINARI, F., GIOSUÈ, S., TUBIELLO, F.N., RETTORI, A., ROSSI, V., SPANNA, F., ROSENZWEIG, C., GULLINO, M.L., Downy mildew (Plasmopara viticola) epidemics on grapevine under climate change (2006) Global Change Biology, 12, pp. 1299-1307; SCHERM, H., VAN BRUGGEN, A.H.C., Global warming and nonlinear growth: How important are changes in average temperature? (1994) Phytopathology, 84, pp. 1380-1384; TUELHER, E.S., OLIVEIRA, E.E., GUEDES, R.N.C., MAGALHÃES, L.C., Ocorrência de bicho-mineiro do cafeeiro (Leucoptera coffeella) influenciada pe